First Department,

September, 1965

(September 7, 1965) The People of the State of New York v. William L. Johnson.

Motion for leave to appeal as a poor person denied. No appeal lies to this court from an order denying reargument. (People v. Smith, 12 A D 2d 667 [2d Dept.].) Concur — Rabin, J. P., Valente, McNally, Eager and Steuer, JJ.
